  "elapsed_s": 9.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "A boy has an affidavit, or is registered, or has chances to get an affidavit is looking for a girl, because of a preference, who has already affidavit.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "Constantly only it's connected, this matrimony and these papers in the towns, with-- with-- with immigration.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "Other people wants to emigrate so  hard, even Hungarian, Hungarian Jews.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "Already they see what's going on and very little.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 38,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "But in order-- in other words, if you had some chance, at least, you  are registered or you have an affidavit, that's already a big step ahead that you'll be able.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So in that paper-- I didn't put my ad in the paper.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I figured out, I knew that nothing will happen.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But it's already was a big step, no dowry, no this, nothing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "A girl-- I had a friend here in America who just emigrated about a few years before.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I write him a letter.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he knew my situation there-- to America, was [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 39,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "I write him a letter, you know my situation?",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I like to have three things from you.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I was naive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Either go to some schooling-- you know, I have all my papers, and maybe I'll continue in America my medical school.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Either you find a girl for me who's coming and willing to marry me, and I-- OK, later on, we'll see what's going to happen.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Maybe she'll be good, maybe she's not-- but the urge of emigration, it's so hard that you [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And the third, there is some talk that if you have $500 to Nicaragua, you can get some visa in Budapest. $500 is a lot of money.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "He gives me a reply.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "I have the letter here, also.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This was already in 1940 in the beginning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 40,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So he tells me-- he  was a nice man.",
      "word_count": 9
    }
  ],
